init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf came and huffed and puffed, but his lungs got cancer from all the uranium.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He thought he would die alone, but the 92nd little pig visited him and was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the wolf said, "I'm sorry I tried to eat you."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So they hung out, and the wolf got better.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He said, "Thank you for taking care of me."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And then the wolf said, "Tonight there's going to be a party at my house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Yeah, and I want you to come.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The pig was excited, so he ran back to his house and got ready for the party.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf and the pig were best friends forever.
